C:\Data\Nucleus_Dev\Vostok_ACU_A\source\XCategory\Application\acu\Processes\JumpIf\JumpIf.c
      1          /**
      2           * @file
      3           * @brief       A cross-category process for determining when to jump to a different step, phase, and/or cycle.
      4           *
      5           * @details
      6           *
      7           * JumpIf Setting File Parameter Data
      8           *
      9           * For a simple jump within the current cycle and phase:
     10           * <pre>
     11           *      Word Offset     First Byte              Second Byte
     12           *      -----------     ---------------         ----------------
     13           *      +0000h          Condition_Index         Statement_Offset
     14           * </pre>
     15           *
     16           * For a jump to a different cycle and/or phase:
     17           * <pre>
     18           *      Word Offset     First Byte              Second Byte
     19           *      -----------     ---------------         ----------------
     20           *      +0000h          Condition_Index         Statement_Offset
     21           *      +0001h          Phase_Offset            Cycle_Offset
     22           * </pre>
     23           *
     24           * For a jump that may return or may have special instructions for estimating:
     25           * <pre>
     26           *      Word Offset     First Byte              Second Byte
     27           *      -----------     ---------------         ----------------
     28           *      +0000h          Condition_Index         Statement_Offset
     29           *      +0001h          Phase_Offset            Cycle_Offset
     30           *      +0002h          Bit 7 = Reerved         0
     31           *                      Bit 6-5 = Predict
     32           * </pre>
     33           *
     34           * Condition Index: An index to the test condition to evaluate. If the condition evaluates to TRUE,
     35           * then the jump occurs. If the condition is FALSE, then no jump occurs.
     36           *
     37           * Cycle Offset: A signed value [-128, 127] that is added to the current cycle to determine the
     38           * target cycle. A value of 0 indicates that there is no change in the cycle. A value of -128
     39           * should be used to set the target cycle to zero.
     40           *
     41           * Phase Offset: A signed value [-128, 127] that is added to the current phase to determine the
     42           * target phase. A value of 0 indicates that there is no change in the phase. A value of -128
     43           * should be used to set the target phase to zero.
     44           *
     45           * Statement Offset: A signed value [-128, 127] that is added to the current statement to determine
     46           * the new location. A value of -128 should be used to set the target statement to zero.
     47           *
     48           * Predict: The prediction field contains instructions on how to interpret the JumpIf behavior
     49           * during cycle time estimation.
     50           *      0 = Predict that the Jump will not occur. Do not evaluate the condition and never jump.
     51           *      1 = Predict that the Jump will occur. Do not evaluate the condition and always jump.
     52           *      2, 3, or unspecified = Evaluate the condition to determine whether or not to jump.
     53           *
     54           *
     55           * $Header: JumpIf.c 1.6 2015/08/05 17:04:36EDT Nelson Ferragut II (FERRANJ) Exp  $
     56           *
     57           * @copyright  Copyright 2014 - $Date: 2015/08/05 17:04:36EDT $  Whirlpool Corporation.  All rights reserved - CONFIDENTIAL.
     58           */
